<text>I would give 0 stars but that is unfortunately not an option. Cube smart as a whole is ok BUT this specific location is horrible.... management (or I should say lack of) is nonexistent, anytime you try to contact someone directly they are never available you will always have to get in touch with their corporate and then corporate will get in touch with management which is just inconvenient. The main reason I am giving this location a 0 is due to our vacate issue. I called corporate (due to not being able to reach the manager)to inform that I would be moving and gave the date corporate explained that they would send an email to the manager to inform and give the date I would be moving and that the manager would reach out to me (which never happened). A few days later I emailed the manager regarding my move and the date because the only email I had received was an auto email reminding me of my payment. She did respond to my email and confirmed my move and sent all information regarding the vacate process. Day of my move my husband pulls up in the uhaul we just rented for 400$ enters our code and it doesn‚Äôt work. We call corporate who then calls the manager and they say the gate is broken and we have to wait till the following day!!!!!!! We were given no notice!!!!! According to the manager it broke the night before which I completely understand things happen but not giving any notice is just completely unprofessional and unacceptable. Luckily uhaul gave us a free day at no charge. Next day I called the corporate office to make sure the gate will be open and when corporate spoke to the emergency contact because manager was unavailable (how convenient) they stated the gate was still down and would be for the next 2 days. My husband had already taken off work and we had already paid for our uhaul I could not even believe that these people do business like this. 1<//rating>
< Review>
No longer a safe complex to live in.

I've lived at this complex for 5 years now going on 6, even upgrading from a 1 bedroom to a 2 bedroom at one point.

My wife lamented to me last night that she no longer feels safe walking the dog around the complex or living here.

In the last year and a half the complex has gone way downhill. We've had car windows broken twice, both times while being parked in the covered parking area.

A man, who the "security" personnel knew about and had already spoken to and called the cops on, went around throwing rocks into multiple cars parked at the complex. The guy was screaming threats at the building for over an hour. Security neither saw nor heard anything.

This place has been rotating through staff so quickly I can't even keep track of who works here anymore. They've also gone through many different security companies. At least now they found one that doesn't actually seem to exist.

They implemented a garbage pickup service recently, but they don't enforce their own policy. Now trash and trash cans sit out in hallways 24/7. You can also see lines of garbage fluid that were dragged through the hallways.

The office staff also let slip that they charge flat fees when people move out, which, you guessed it, is illegal in California.

The good: The maintenance staff is extremely nice and they do good work. They are also consistently employed so you get to know them, and they know their stuff.

The grounds are green. One of the reasons we liked the complex was the trees and the grass. We also used to brag about how safe the area was.</Review>

I lived there for 1.5 years and it started off fine. I paid no water, no trash disposal,  and no sewage. The rent was 1196, the walls lots of chipped paint from over painting, and mold on the tub ,but other than that it seemed to be fine. When I renewed my lease my rent went up $50 and in addition I had to start paying for water,  trash disposal, and sewage. When I moved out I cleaned my place top to bottom very well and thorough to avoid any reason to not get my security deposit back. I turned my keys in and about 2 weeks later I received a statement of Deposit from alvista claiming to have taken money out of my deposit for painting,  carpet cleaning,  and house cleaning. I received around $115 out of $500. I contacted the manager via email because that's how they handle their disputes but I wanted to know why they charged me so much money. I felt robbed!  I received a response from the manager days later stating that it cost them more than what they charged and asked if I would like a new statement of Deposit for the amount due. < Review>
I lived at Alvista for 2 years and it was just okay. The office staff is friendly, but ineffective. I complained several times about a neighbor who was locking up her dog for 10-12 hours a day and letting it bark and howl all day long. The when I talked to office staff they always took the time to make note of my complaints, but ultimately nothing was ever done about the dog.

The doors are very heavy and often slam loudly. Most of my neighbors were respectful and made sure they closed the door by hand, but some neighbors went in and out at all times of the night letting that door slam. I lost count of how many times I was jolted awake at night by a crashing, slamming door.

They were very good at cracking down on smokers and people who don't pick after their dogs, and I really appreciated that. There was always plenty of parking, and in general I always felt safe here, even on the first floor. It's a great place to live if you have a dog, and they even have a large fenced area to let dogs off leash.

I think if they can install a device on the apartment doors to prevent them from slamming, it would be a much nicer place to live. This seems like such a little thing, but to be jolted awake, or even just startled by that crashing door made my experience at Alvista less than perfect.

In response to the reviewers who complained about not getting their full deposit back... the lease is very clear about the charges on move out. If you live there for less than two years, there are some charges the renter is responsible for. Ask questions and read your lease to avoid misunderstandings.

Full disclosure, I didn't clean anything before I left. I was moving back to Minnesota and I didn't have time. I gave them a $750 deposit and got back $507. This was more than satisfactory for me.</Review>

< review>
Where do I start with this place... the reason we picked this complex was the dog park, which is great! Most people who go there are super friendly and have awesome dogs! But that's about all we care for and there has been talk about the big dog park being removed for a new leasing office... the staff here is nice don't get me wrong but they are terrible. My water was cold for two months and my tub leaked for three. My smoke detector went off every time I used the damn oven before it even had food in it because of the heat and I had windows open and all fans on! My bedroom smells like weed 70% of the time because of our neighbors and the office hasn't done anything, the walls are painted with the shittiest paint I've ever seen, every door and drawer in this place was painted and then closed and opened so the paint is clumped, torn, and sticks. All the windows and the cocking around the shower are moldy ,and my tub has had a Chunk missing since we moved in and when maintenance came to stop the tub from dripping they didn't do anything about it. let me tell you I'm a clean freak and have tried cleaning the mold from them. They have no way to enforce people to clean up after pets so every grassy area is full of dog crap! There is always atleast 2 dryers down or a washing machine. They spend so much time and I'm sure money on redoing the grounds and stupid concrete that they seriously neglect the appartments. I constantly have water pressure issues now too. It seems to me and my dog park buddies that this complex cares more about getting new renters than keeping the ones they have which is a shame because we love the location and my dogs have made friends here and so have I. I really hope the staff gets it together and tries to improve the apts without trying to keep upping the rent... with such poor resident satisfaction , or at least make sure they fix the problems in a timely and efficient Manor. I never write reviews and I'm sorry it's all over the place but I wish I had seen more when I found this place so I hope this helps some of you weigh out your options better.< /review>

But our experience has not been great living here. One thing that attracted us to alvista is that they are dog friendly. However, in the common areas, people let their dogs poop all over the place and don't bother to pick it up. Disgusting and a super way for diseases to spread, pretty sure you don't want your dog to get sick right? Then there's a pool and jacuzzi. Several in the massive complex in fact. Cool! Not! Oh and we resigned a lease only because they notified us that we needed to resign it without much notice and that our rent was being raised. We are currently looking for a new place. Well I'm guessing their business practices are better at these other places if nothing else and most likely have done more then slap a new coat of paint on them and jack up the rents. Alvista on Baltimore is a true facade. Looks nice till you live here. Don't fall for it. Don't rent here. Don't waste your time or money.<//review>

<Review>We went to Aashiyana with friends on Saturday, and had a very bad experience. While the food at Aashiyana is good, the experience wasn't.

The serving lady was rude, which she was the last time we went as well. We were having a nice meal when my 1 year old woke up all cranky, and efforts to soothe her weren't helping. A little while later, the serving lady came upto us and asked us, in her usual rude manner, to get the baby to quiet down because their guests were getting disturbed. I assume she was talking about the guests in their banquet hall because the diners in the restaurant did not seem affected. Kids cry, that's what they do. My husband, a little annoyed with her "request" said that we were doing all we could, we don't enjoy our baby crying either. There were four kids at our table, none of them running around, none of them being rowdy, just one who was crying- something that kids do!

Once the meal ended, however, and it was time to leave, our friend asked to see the manager to tell them about this incident, and the manager, instead of apologizing, started telling us how to parent by telling us that he saw us and we did nothing to calm the baby down (Umm...hello?! We took her out, but we don't owe you an explanation), and how when his kids were little he always knew how to handle their crying and, among other things, he said 'agar bache paalne nahin aate toh paida kyun karte hain' (If you don't know how to raise kids, why do you have them?). That was the worst! Nobody is allowed to say something like that to anyone, ever!

I have to say that we have dined with our kids at many different places, some fancy, some not, and we have never been spoken to this way, or been told to get our kids to quiet down when they cried. This has got to be our worst experience ever. Aashiyana had no signs that said children under a certain age weren't allowed there. If you allow children in, you're a family restaurant, and this is what happens when families dine at your restaurant- kids cry- and as a restaurant that caters to everyone, you have got to deal with it.

Very upsetting experience. Never going back there. If the management is reading this, please train your staff better, and ask them to keep their parenting opinions to themselves. Thank you.</Review><pics>None<//pics><resp>None<//resp><GmapID>0x80c32c68bb8cc53d:0xcc078632d5f5351e< /GmapID></record>

< review>
Excellent Pakistani Food. Excellent Beef and Chicken Dishes. Much better than several restaurants in the neighborhood. I have eaten at all of them many times.
The above remarks are from late 2016 or early 2017. Same management stills runs the place. I dont think they have ever repainted it.

October 24, 2018
I called ahead and inquired about daily specials  Paya was recommended. I asked if there were beef pieces in it  I was told "Absolutely".

There was not a shred of beef in the dish. It was most generic and tasteless Payas I have ever eaten. This dish was not bad tasting.  It had no taste. It had less taste than a coated aspirin pill.

I conveyed my feelings to another server and asked if I could get a small side order of Dal for a charge, of course. Without the slightest of concern I was told my only option was a full order of Dal.

I had above average food here several times. Don't expect any courtesy. Even if you vomit, the restaurant will insist on full payment and for sure not offer to swap your dish/s. No way, not in this life time.

They may be in United States  They have learned nothing.<//review>

Place is decent. There's always a few dryers that are out of order. Ladies who work there are not the friendliest. This place is always packed unless you come later at night. However i do like that they have 80lb washers and you can get all your clothes done in one wash. They have a customer restroom as well. < review>
I'm updating the review from 5 stars to 3.
I normally would give 5 stars to Bonchon as I loved them since the beginning. I'm also glad there is one in San Mateo instead of the Sunnyvale location which is much further. However, I'm taking off 2 stars because the spicy flavor is completely off. It's almost NOT spicy at all. When I get them from Sunnyvale the spicy ones have more red chili specks and tastes much better. There is already a choice for people who doesn't like spicy but for those who choose the spicy flavor, make the wings as spicy as it should have been. I'm also upset that last time I ordered 2 combos where I asked 1 to be half and half and the other to be all spicy, the ones I got are both half and half. The only good thing about this location is that they do prepare food quickly.  The picture can show you how the spicy one looks like as you can tell there is barely any sauce on the chicken.<//review>

< text>
The chicken was fresh and super crispy, but that's about all there was going for it. The sauce was mediocre (and there wasn't much of it on the chicken at that). And the chicken strips were dry. The food is way overpriced considering how forgettable it tasted.

Service was okay. They were nice, but I felt rushed at times. It certainly wasn't good enough to warrant an automatic 15% tip (we were a party of 2).

No reason to come back. There are tastier options (that offer better value too) in San Mateo.</text>

< Text>
Good flavors although the chicken was a bit on the dryer side and thinner than expected but did have a good crunchy coating. I liked the soy garlic sauce more than the spicy. I ordered the 10 piece 50/50 ($13.95) and that comes with cole slaw (good and fresh) or pickled radish (no substitutions) which is easily enough for two or a really hungry person. They weren't very hot when served and neither was the steamed rice ($2.25) and they claim it's made to order (up to 30 minutes) but I think mine came out in less than 10.

Service was attentive for the most part. Automatic 15% gratuity included for everyone. Draft beers are $5 (Sapporo, Lagunitas IPA, Blue Moon, California Lager)
Happy hour $4 drafts (M-F 430-6). There's a couple of TVs.< /Text>

<Pics>None<//Pics>< review>
Bonchon Chicken is a Korean Style fried chicken spot. They serve Wings (wings and drummets) or Drums. They offer 2 flavors: Spicy or Soy Garlic. You can't go wrong with either flavor. Personally i think the soy garlic is more flavorful, but i prefer spicy because i just like spicy foods. The chicken comes out hot and fresh. The outside has a crisy texture  while the inside is very moist. The service is is very good, they check up on you often and refill my water a couple times without me needing to wave them over.<//review>

<rate>4<//rate>< Review>
chain korean fried chicken restaurant locates in san mateo downtown, 2nd ave and B street (former tea river) the fried chicken is legit, crispy skin layer and good texture on meat. You can choose from wings, drums and stripes with garlic soy, spicy or half n half flavor. They have bar area and about 7-8 tables inside, no outdoor seating. They offer lunch special which is good for people working nearby. I visited during their soft opening and it seems this is a must try spot in San Mateo for fried chicken lovers.< /Review>

<Rating>5<//Rating>< Text>
Had a great experience here today; I was a bit nervous before going, after reading some of the reviews, but didn't have much choice as nothing nearby was open on the weekends.

I had a flat tire, and called ahead to ask if I could have my car towed there--the woman on the phone was very helpful and friendly and said to bring it on over, and that they actually have my size tire in stock. In the past at other shops I've had to wait several days because my tire needed to be ordered (Smart car), so that was a nice surprise.

When I got there she was up-front about costs and honest about how long it'd take. I walked home thinking I probably wouldn't have my car back today, but 2 hours later she called to tell me it was ready! Very happy customer, and I'd definitely go back again if necessary.</Text>

<Response>None< /Response><Rate>1</Rate>< review>
Our experience suggests this business is not trustworthy.  My wife asked them to repair her front right tire which had a slow leak because of a nail.  They called her a few hours later and told her the tire was not repairable (2 nails) and that she would need to buy 2 new tires at $298 each because the vehicle is all-wheel-drive (the difference in tread depth between a new tire and the existing tire was only 2/32").  We declined the work and were charged $30 for their attempted repair and for putting on the spare tire.  As we were driving away I discovered they didn't put the damaged tire back in the vehicle.  I had to go back and ask for it.

The following weekend we went to America's Tire in Redwood City for a second opinion because our experience with Wheel Works didn't feel right.  America's Tire tested the tire Wheel Works had repaired and told us it was fine.  They charged us zero for this service.  They said we didn't need to replace the tire, which incidentally was selling for $99 less at America's Tire.  The automobile dealer's service department also informed me we didn't need 2 new tires because the 2/32" difference in tread depth would not cause a mechanical problem with the car.  Our experience suggests Wheel Works was trying to "churn" business or take advantage of a woman and at the same time trying to keep (and probably resell) the tire that they repaired.

Forgot to mention the America's Tire tech told me the bolt holding the spare tire down inside the vehicle was bent as though someone tried to pull the tire out without realizing they had to first unscrew the bolt.  The only time the spare was ever touched was when Wheel Works removed it for the above repair.  Avoid this Wheel Works location.< /review>

<user_id>113214293021196059339<//user_id>< Review>
I love this place. My dog loves this place. She gets to be in her element. Be a dog. Run with her wolf packs, play and swim! But she still has to have manners, respect for people and othe dogs. However there are what appears to be several people living out of
a blue and white van with a few dogs. I don't care so much that they're there everyday, for the last two months, but I'm bothered by the fact they have dogs that have started to take ownership of the dog park! They started out good dogs, friendly dogs. Today, I expierenced the owner of one yell and stomp her feet at my dog as we were approaching my vehicle. All the while yelling at her dog to stay. I kindly told her perhaps she shouldn't bring an aggressive dog to the "off leash dog park." She snapped back, "he's fine as long as no dogs come near him. This is not acceptable to me. I did not call the authorities as nothing had happened, however, I should not fear my dog's health. I will in fact be reporting to Animal Control. I'm not placing any blame on the dog..doesn't matter to me the breed, but the owners must take responsibility. Not the 99% of us that expect cooperation when suggesting they take their dog elsewhere. I'm sorry they're living outta their van. But at 100 + degree weather, this is unfair and inhumane to their dog.< /Review>

111831819855656776135</user>
<Name>Vasily Geyko<//Name><Time>1551589925513< /Time><rate>5< /rate>< Review>
It is a good small family business car repair shop! As a consequence of that, you should not expect to enjoy a luxurious waiting lobby with TV, coffee, and muffins while your car is being fixed, like in a dealership. All these is paid back buy the quality and the price of their service though. They are very customer oriented and try to do their job well at lowest possible price.
They are careful in picking up parts, so that the parts will have a year warranty, which is important, especially if you need to disassemble half of the car to get there. They are very friendy, and once they even fixed a minor scratch on my car for free.
If you want to do some minor car fix, such as oil change, you better arrive earlier, something like 8:50 am or so, as they open at 9 and you will be the first one served. If you want something significant you just leave your car there and take a Bart train from Union City, which is about 10 minutes walking distance.</Review>

<Rating>5< /Rating><review>On Xmas Eve 2018 I arrived into Union City, from Colorado, with a knocking sound emanating from the front end of my 2006 RAM 3500 4x4.  I called Escutia's, based on all the great reviews, and he took me in right away. He immediately diagnosed the problem as a worn-out u-joint on the front axle and ordered OEM quality replacements parts, which he put on the day after Xmas.

<text>I've been working on cars for many decades and it's rare that I need a mechanic. Yet there are some tasks I can't do either because they need very specialized equipment or I'm prohibited by law from doing without certification. I was glad to find a mechanic who is knowledgeable, honest, and affordable. It always bothered me that there are mechanics who do jobs that I know take very little time, yet they manage to charge people exorbitant amounts for labor, and round up to charge for hours that they didn't really work, "preventive" services that are not needed, or parts that don't really need changing.  Escutia charges rates that are very fair. I finally got to the point that I was willing to have a mechanic do things for me out of convenience, such as tune ups, rather than doing it myself since I wasn't being ripped off with high prices.

The flip side is that they have plenty of local business and never needed to advertise, so the place looks like the last place I expected to take my car. It's the site of an old former  two pump gas station with an unprofessionally hand painted sign hanging over it, and is entirely out of character from what you'd expect from a place that gives quality service.<//text>< Date>

<Rate>2</Rate><review>I give 2 stars instead of one only because the server started out good, and the food showed up fast and right.

I never did like this dennys location. Common issues were always bad service, bad food prep and lack of ambience. Today was only slightly different. I was seated and it took close to 15 minutes to get a server to stop by. I almost left. Then the server who showed up looked like an off duty server who was helping out. Again...I let it go. She was personable and just a bit chatty. I am chatty too, so I liked that. Food showed up fast. Eggs were right and the server was professional. There.. that covers 5 stars. Now the deductions down to 2 stars.

As soon as she completed my order she went on break. No problem, other servers will watch for me. Yeah, right.

I finished my coffee, put the cup on the edge of table for a refill. This is a common signal for a refill. I've travelled around the country and overseas...this really is a signal. Servers walked past my table a half dozen times and ignored it. I had to ask a busser to refill my coffee. No one came through to check on me. Maybe I wanted a slice of purple or something.

I dont know why this location is so bad. I can go to the one in mission valley or la mesa and have good service. But here... I can bet money that it will be bad. I dont get it.

As for the stellar reviews ... I just listened to a report on NPR about a website where you can trade or buy positive reviews for you business. I guess dennys invests in that service.</review>< Pictures>

<Review>Your typical Denny's diner. We usually go with 5 to 7 people and are always seated within 10 minutes. They turn tables pretty quickly and there is plenty of room in the restaurant. Once you're seated, your service depends on how busy it is. Majority of time they are quick and efficient. One server used to remember all 7 orders to a T. I dont think she's there anymore. Thwre are times that service is inadequate. Not necessarily bad just kind of forgetful and quite entertaining. You'll start getting food you didn't order, sodas arriving when you still have one. An extra coffee. Like they are so scared of being slower that they start sending stuff early-just sending things to everyone. Otherwise food is a decent diner meal and the price isn't something to complain about.<//Review>< Pictures>
